  {emoji:"🎆",name:"Carnival & New Year Celebrations",location:"Promenade Beach & throughout — December/January",desc:"Puducherry's New Year celebration reflects its dual French-Tamil character — on New Year's Eve, the Promenade Beach fills with revellers; the French Quarter's cafes and restaurants serve elaborate menus; the Sri Aurobindo Ashram's bells ring at midnight; and the Tamil families of Ville Noire celebrate with their own customs. The small Puducherry Carnival (usually December) reflects the French colonial tradition of public celebration — street theatre, music and food in the streets of the White Town."},
