  {emoji:"🍷",name:"Pondicherry Wine & Beer Culture",location:"French Quarter restaurants & bars",desc:"Puducherry has the most liberal alcohol licensing in South India — a legacy of French rule that made wine and beer part of everyday life. The result is that Puducherry has India's finest wine restaurant culture outside Delhi and Mumbai. French wines, local craft beers and Indian wines are served openly in the White Town's restaurants. The locally produced Arclite beer, the estate wines served at heritage hotel restaurants, and the wine bars of the French Quarter create an evening culture sophisticated by any international standard."},
